Consolidated Facemoji User Feedback
1. AI Features Feel Intrusive and Unnecessary

Many users feel AI features are pushed into the keyboard experience rather than being optional.

Representative feedback

“The AI slop keeps getting shoved down my throat.”

“AI constantly gets in the way of my quick select.”

“Features you can’t turn off without disabling ones that actually help.”

“Search suggestion doesn’t actually search, it sends you to another site.”

Underlying sentiment
Users feel that AI features interrupt the typing experience and are not clearly useful.

2. Keyboard Reliability Issues

A large portion of feedback focuses on basic keyboard functionality breaking.

Common problems mentioned

Keyboard glitches:

Keyboard disappearing while typing

Keyboard refusing to pop up

Keyboard shrinking to a tiny size

Keys requiring multiple presses

Keyboard stuck in lowercase

Emoji and typing problems:

Emojis randomly disappearing

Unable to access emoji keyboard

Random font changes

Crashes:

Keyboard stops typing entirely

App crashes or freezes

Representative feedback

“The keyboard keeps dropping and refusing to come back up.”

“Keys have to be pressed multiple times.”

“The keyboard makes itself miniscule.”

“It just sometimes doesn't work properly.”

Underlying sentiment
Users expect 100% reliability from a keyboard, and instability quickly leads to uninstalling the app.

3. Weak Autocorrect and Voice Typing

Users frequently complain about text prediction quality.

Common complaints

Incorrect word suggestions

Poor swipe typing accuracy

Voice typing errors

Lack of punctuation in voice input

Representative feedback

“Autocorrect suggests the wrong words.”

“Swipe-to-text is inaccurate.”

“Voice typing gets things wrong half the time.”

Underlying sentiment
Users compare Facemoji to Gboard and SwiftKey, which have stronger language prediction.

4. Missing Core Productivity Features

Users mention several standard keyboard features they expect but cannot find.

Requested features include:

Undo / redo

Easier toolbar customization

Better keyboard switching

More visible editing tools

Image background alignment lock

Representative feedback

“The only thing it's missing is undo and redo.”

“It would need to be more visible and accessible.”

Underlying sentiment
Users want more functional editing tools, not just customization.

5. Excessive Advertising

Users frequently complain about the number of ads required to access content.

Representative feedback

“Endless ads just to see one sticker.”

“Eight ads just to see one creation.”

Underlying sentiment
The ad system feels excessive and frustrating, especially when content is not delivered after viewing ads.

6. Loss of User Data and Customizations

Some users report losing their created keyboards, themes, or saved items.

Examples include:

Themes disappearing after reinstalling

Custom keyboards missing

Saved content not syncing with accounts

Representative feedback

“All my keyboards are gone.”

“What’s the point of logging in if my themes disappear?”

Underlying sentiment
Users expect cloud syncing and account protection for their creations.

7. Emoji, Font, and Compatibility Issues

Users report compatibility problems when sending stylized text or fonts.

Common issues include:

Some emojis missing

Fonts displaying as question marks on other devices

Special characters not supported by messaging apps

Representative feedback

“When I use certain fonts the other person only sees question marks.”

“Messages with emojis and special characters may not display correctly.”

Underlying sentiment
Fancy fonts and emojis can cause cross-device compatibility issues.

8. Customization Limitations

Although customization is a core feature of Facemoji, users feel options are too restricted.

Requests include:

More free fonts

More free themes

Blank keyboard backgrounds

Ability to edit emojis and stickers

Better search for keyboard themes

Representative feedback

“Most fonts are now premium.”

“Options are very limited if you want a blank background.”

Underlying sentiment
Customization is a key reason people use the app, so limitations reduce satisfaction.

9. Feature Control and Settings Problems

Users report difficulty controlling keyboard features.

Examples include:

Fancy fonts turning back on automatically

Having to repeatedly switch keyboards in settings

Toolbar customization being unclear

Representative feedback

“Fancy fonts keep turning themselves back on.”

“You have to go to settings every time to switch keyboards.”

Underlying sentiment
Users want clear and persistent control over keyboard settings.

10. Sticker and Emoji Creation Limitations

Users want more creative tools.

Requested features:

Create custom stickers

Edit emojis

Better sticker compatibility across apps

Representative feedback

“Let users edit their own emojis and stickers.”

“Stickers won’t work on my phone.”

Underlying sentiment
Users want more creativity and personalization tools.

11. Performance and Background Usage

Some users report performance issues affecting their phone.

Examples:

High background usage

Keyboard slowing down device performance

Representative feedback

“The app has been having too much background usage.”

Underlying sentiment
Users worry the keyboard consumes too many system resources.

Overall Sentiment Summary

Users generally like:

Keyboard themes

Custom fonts

Emoji and sticker variety

Personalization features

However, satisfaction drops due to:

Reliability issues

Weak typing intelligence

Intrusive AI features

Excessive ads

Loss of user-created content